valid_variations.reason: UBX-CFG-MSG defines a specific Poll Request payload (2 bytes: Class, ID) distinct from the Set/Get payload (8 bytes: Class, ID, Rates). Both are valid definitions appearing in documentation, but the 8-byte definition is canonical for data representation.

adjudication.reasoning: This message (UBX-CFG-MSG) has two distinct payload definitions in the protocol: a 'Poll Request' (2 bytes, containing Class/ID to query) and a 'Set/Get' configuration (8 bytes, containing Class/ID and rate array). Extractions 1, 3, and 6 captured the full Set/Get structure, which is chosen as canonical because it describes the configuration data fields. The other extractions captured the Poll Request structure. While these are accurate reflections of the Polling mechanism described in the manuals, they are marked as 'valid_variation' because they do not describe the actual configuration data structure.
